  => "premise: atlas.n6 contains 2692 directed arrows (1810 <- + 882 ->) over 6760 @C+@R nodes — density 0.398"
  => "today's reality: every multi-hop relation is HAND-COMPUTED into prose strings"
  => "evidence: lines 28/34/43 — 'meta-closure: 15 grade-10 derivations (sigma,phi,tau,sopfr,...)' is a LITERAL transitive closure baked into a => prose row because no primitive exists"
  => "axis-I reifies that hand-computation as a DSL primitive belonging to atlas.n6 itself"

